.TH HSH 1 "Simple Shell" "Holberton School"
.SH NAME
hsh \- simple UNIX command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
[\fIFILE\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple UNIX shell that reads commands from standard input and executes them.

The shell works in both interactive and non-interactive modes. It supports command execution using the PATH environment variable and handles basic process creation.

.SH INVOCATION
Interactive mode:
.PP
.nf
$ ./hsh
($)
.fi

Non-interactive mode:
.PP
.nf
$ echo "ls" | ./hsh
.fi

.SH BUILTINS
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
The shell uses the following environment variables:
.TP
.B PATH
Directories in which the shell searches for executable files.

.SH RETURN VALUE
The shell returns 0 on success, or the exit status of the last executed command.

.SH AUTHOR
Written by Holberton School students.

.SH SEE ALSO
sh(1), execve(2), fork(2), wait(2)
